description:
Wherever you find a person willing to do a days work for a days living you can usually find someone else, plotting ways to take it from them.&nbsp;
Some people call this survival of the fittest, but most of us have a different word for it: crime.&nbsp;
The Firm are the gangsters and organised criminals of Ulaya. Protection racketeering, theft, robbery, banditry, the sale and supply of illicit substances and services: all of these things are their stock and trade. Violent brutality and ruthlessness permeate all that they do.&nbsp;
The true extent of their power is not known, and few are brave or foolhardy enough to find out&hellip;

&mdash;description from the pulbisher

Treasure hunters, tomb robbers, adventurers, scavengers and rogues: an Artefacter cuts a glamorous, but undoubtedly nefarious, figure. Often dashing, brave to the point of recklessness, and willing to risk their life for personal gain. They can be found wandering the wilds for valuable artefacts from a bygone age, from which, they hope to become fabulously rich...&nbsp;
However, there is more to these ambiguous figures than the mercenary opportunist image they project. Underneath the gloss of avarice and roguish indifference lies a secret&hellip;&nbsp;
Few know the truth, but there are rumours that the Artefacters hold to a higher purpose. There are even whispers that they are agents of the &lsquo;New Enlightenment&rsquo;...

&mdash;description from the publisher

Over last 9 years since premiere author of "Show Business" has been listening carefully to below complaints of the players:
- The game is too long;
- The rulebook is a nightmare;
- There's no Player Aid;
- For such heavy economic game the luck factor is unacceptable;
- The prints on Trend dice wipe off.

And here you go! "Tycoons" - the expansion to "Show Business" responds to all above complaints and delivers:

- A deck of brand new cards with 6 new, very powerful CHARACTERS along with compatibility reprint of 80 cards from basic game;
- Completely redesigned, improved and reprinted Rulebook of basic game (hope this time it will be the fastest comprehensible reading ever :-) );
- Brand new Player Aids;
- Fine tuning of elements that made first edition of "Show Business" a bit chaotic and luck dependent (due to unpredictible hostile actions and overall randomness). Now the game gives much more support to counteract hostile actions of your opponents and concentrate steadily on career of your band.
- 3 different time scenarios: short for newbies (40 to 100 min), medium for regular players (60 to 150 min) and extended for fans (80 to 200 min). The low values show play time for 2 players the high for 5. Decide yourself how much time you want to play and go on;
- Stickers for Trend Dice.

"Tycoons" will be distributed as a standalone package for owners of basic game as well as an expansion integrated in one box with basic "Show Business".
Give it a second chance or brand new try and enjoy!

In a world full of terrifying dangers, independent settlements are particularly vulnerable to attack. Without any sort of formal defence force it often falls on communities to organise protection amongst themselves. The bravest and most proficient citizens form a volunteer force of enthusiastic amateurs, who serve as much time as they can, protecting others against the many dangers which their community face.&nbsp;

These are the Militias: patrolling the nearby countryside, maintaining fortifications and defending their way of life against all those who threaten them.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Two Khans is a quick hidden identity and deduction game based on intelligence, accuracy and quick awareness.

In this game time is against you and each player only knows the identity of ONE other player. Now it&rsquo;s up to players to figure out who&rsquo;s who and find their way to find Khans. Whichever team first finds and kills the other team&rsquo;s Khan, wins.

Story: The story goes back to thousands years ago in Persia, where the king is dying and has no relative successor to take the throne. If the king dies, his Senior Minister will take the throne but the problem is that the king does not trust any of his staff, specially the Senior Minister! So he writes two secret letter to the two famous khans of north and south, explaining the reason and inviting them to his palace&hellip;

As Mr. Nasty, the infamous innkeeper, you give customers a simple promise: a stiff drink, soft bed, and swift kick in the pants for those who start trouble. You won&rsquo;t sell large goods at the piers like other merchants in town. Instead, you&rsquo;ll offer room and board to tired adventurers after the markets close for the day. But space is limited and customers are fussy&mdash;the last thing you want is folks yapping about a bad experience&hellip;

The Innkeeper is a new merchant you can play as. It is centered around a speculation game, where you try to prepare rooms for the most common adventurers in play at the end of each round. If you plan well and satisfy your guests, you can yield an ever-increasing income. However, if you fail, you can expect brawls to break out&mdash;which can hurt your business!

&mdash;description from the publisher

&ldquo;The next dimension in word gaming&rdquo;

TrapWords is easy to play yet complex to master. Earn points by forming words in all directions: straight lines, staggered, reversed or turned upside down. Only those who excel at splitting or closing word &ldquo;traps&rdquo; will emerge victorious.

&mdash;description from the publisher

There are many different kinds of mercenary, but perhaps the most feared are the bounty hunters who ask no questions: The United League of Bondsmen.&nbsp;
A Bondsman may tell you he is part of a great tradition of hunting down transgressors and dangerous criminals, but the truth is quite different. Their only qualification is brutality, martial skill and a complete lack of moral qualms. Officially they are bounty hunters and thief takers. In reality more often than not they are slave-catchers, assassins and hired muscle.&nbsp;
Their motto speaks for itself. For the Bondsman, cash talks, and the question &ldquo;why?&rdquo; is a mere formality.

&mdash;description from the publisher

The Autarchs are sadistic creatures.
You should know, being one of them. Galactic Wars have made you the rulers of the known worlds, but now the High Autarch is seeking a new, worthy pastime. Welcome to the Age of Blood and Glory, where you and your opponents will send your fighters to the epic re-enactments of the infamous wars, in the hope of finding favour with the High Autarch.

Autarch: The Age of Blood and Glory is an asymmetric PvP arena combat miniature tabletop for 1-4 players, also playable as skirmish, with additional worker placement preparation phase which builds the campaign potential of the game.

With two games in one, your journey will alter between merciless arena battles, based on unique dice-less card combat, providing both a macabre and fun experience; and worker-placement phases, where you will strategize your next steps in a push-your-luck environment.

Battles are played in a modular arena with different fighter races, developed by advanced deck-building through character leveling and equipping different items. Main mechanics which make up the unique and challenging experience of Autarch include:

     Initiative Dial mechanism creates a dynamic player order, depending on the played cards;
     Threat Level defines how much each fighter is worth in every attack, making it less opportunistic to focus on the weaker ones;
     Dice-replacement Power deck represents effort a player is willing to invest in all of his actions. As both the attacker and the defender will have to use Power, you will not only have to make trade offs between offense and defense, but also test your bluffing skills in an effort to read through your opponent&rsquo;s secret intentions;
     Player&rsquo;s hand being the target of attacks (selected randomly by opponents during successful attacks), with your initial hand being comprised of combat- and defense cards, and clogged with wounds as you get damaged, which may inflict you with permanent injuries. 


&mdash;description from the publisher
